==English==
===Etymology===
From French for [[mailboat]].  First used in Great Britain in 1894, the term was adopted for general use by the Universal Postal Union in 1897.

===Noun===
'''paquebot'''
# a mailboat
# ''(Postal history):'' a [[postal marking]] or [[cancellation]] stamped on mail posted at sea or ia a harbour for procesing by the [[postal]] authorities at the next port of call.  Mail so marked in one country will often carry the stamps of another country.

===Adjective===
#Relating to mail posted at sea.
#: a '''paquebot''' letter, a '''paquebot''' [[duplex]].

